REVISION:
1. What is Page Object Model and what are it's benefits?
   - POM is a design principle where we create a Java Class for each page of the website;
   - we use this Class to store all of the Web Elements on the page and any methods, that may use the Web Elements;
3. Also helps to avoid code redundancy - we can reuse the same methods multiple times
In different scenarios. The page classes essentially function as a “CommonMethods”
Class for the page.
4. Improves maintenance - By organizing the pages into class we can easily find
Exactly what method is failing. “Where any failures are”
5. Helps to keep the framework scalable. We can constantly grow and expand it